sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: TAL repressor 1 expression under the control of a pBAD promoter and a theophylline riboswitch inducible by arabinose and theophylline.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pBAD is a part from the registry. The riboswitch is from the Gallivan Lab's paper Synthetic riboswitches that induce gene expression in diverse bacterial species. by Topp et al. in Appl Environ Microbiol. The TAL repressor is from the Segal Lab at the UC Davis Genome Center. See their paper Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects. by Meckler et al. submitted to Nucleic Acids Res.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There cannot be a scar between the end of the riboswitch and the start codon of the TAL repressor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Encodes a RNA secondary structure that in the presence of theophylline undergoes a conformational change that makes available the previously sequestered RBS, thus allowing transcription of the downstream sequence. Achieves a 60-fold activation ratio in 2mM theophylline as reported by Topp et al. in: 'Synthetic Riboswitches That Induce Gene Expression in Diverse Bacterial Species.' Appl. Environ. Microbiol. December 2010 vol. 76 no. 23 7881-7884
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aura Ferreiro
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Appl. Environ. Microbiol. December 2010 vol. 76 no. 23 7881-7884. Synthetic riboswitch generated through rational design and in vivo screening.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription activator-like (TAL) repressor DNA binding protein that binds to a specific DNA sequence, called TALe Binding Site 1 (TBS 1) (part BBa_K1212003). Low binding affinity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Assembled in the Segal Lab at the UC Davis Genome Center. See Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects by Meckler et al. submitted to Nucleic Acids Research.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.
